WEBVTT

00:29.217 --> 00:30.302
IN YOUR RADIANT SEASON

00:33.388 --> 00:35.014
CHARACTERS, EVENTS, ORGANIZATIONS,
AND PLACES IN THIS DRAMA ARE FICTITIOUS

00:35.015 --> 00:36.308
ALL CHILD ACTORS AND ANIMALS
FILMED IN A SAFE ENVIRONMENT

00:38.644 --> 00:40.479
Mom, don't go.

00:41.355 --> 00:42.522
Let me come with you!

00:45.567 --> 00:47.693
Mom…

00:51.698 --> 00:53.283
Let me keep this, Dad.

00:54.910 --> 00:56.995
Dad…

00:59.664 --> 01:02.958
You shouldn't accept kids
without their parents' permission!

01:02.959 --> 01:04.878
- I…
- Come with me.

01:11.760 --> 01:12.843
Okay.

01:12.844 --> 01:14.970
Dad! Dad!

01:14.971 --> 01:17.349
I promise not to draw anymore, so…

01:18.225 --> 01:19.810
So please let me stay in Korea.

01:24.147 --> 01:27.025
EPISODE 3

01:46.002 --> 01:47.587
I'll see you. Excuse me.

02:04.938 --> 02:07.023
Are you using this room by yourself?

02:08.525 --> 02:11.486
No, I have a roommate,
but he's traveling right now.

02:13.780 --> 02:14.865
Do you want a drink?

02:35.886 --> 02:37.429
Father…

02:43.810 --> 02:45.770
That's just…

03:41.409 --> 03:43.536
How long are you going to keep doing this?

03:43.537 --> 03:46.289
What more do I have to do
to make you stop?

04:40.385 --> 04:42.387
I kept forcing myself to hang on,

04:43.430 --> 04:46.057
but I couldn't find
any reason to keep going,

04:46.766 --> 04:49.394
so I eventually decided to end it all.

04:55.984 --> 05:00.112
But then she disturbed me really loudly.

05:08.705 --> 05:10.164
Ran
CHAN, CHAN, CHAN!

05:10.165 --> 05:11.248
Oh…

05:11.249 --> 05:12.833
The pen you sent me
for my birthday…

05:12.834 --> 05:16.921
I used it to draw a design,
and it won in our company contest!

05:16.922 --> 05:19.506
- Let's go!
-  It won?

05:19.507 --> 05:21.592
Thank you so much!

05:21.593 --> 05:22.594
You know,

05:23.178 --> 05:24.721
you're my savior.

05:25.722 --> 05:26.765
"You're…

05:29.517 --> 05:30.560
my savior."

05:31.227 --> 05:34.564
And that disruption
gave me an opportunity.

05:35.440 --> 05:37.733
An opportunity to live again.

05:41.321 --> 05:42.322
Ran
DARN IT!

05:46.660 --> 05:48.661
Oh, gosh. They said it's a fake.

05:48.662 --> 05:51.914
That Gold-something that helps you sleep.
I heard there's no proof.

05:51.915 --> 05:53.624
I should've looked into it
before telling you.

06:14.604 --> 06:17.147
Why did it suddenly get so lively?

06:17.148 --> 06:19.608
It's like music to wake you up.

06:19.609 --> 06:21.194
I'm so sorry.

06:30.203 --> 06:31.578
Shocking news.

06:31.579 --> 06:33.872
I was eating lunch with my teammates,

06:33.873 --> 06:35.124
and there was…

06:35.125 --> 06:37.084
dun dun, eggplant in it.

06:37.085 --> 06:38.211
Gross.

06:40.547 --> 06:41.630
Eggplant?

06:41.631 --> 06:45.509
It's all mushy and squishy,
and it's neon-colored. Yuck!

06:45.510 --> 06:47.052
The taste of a neon alien.

06:56.813 --> 06:57.897
Mmm.

06:59.899 --> 07:01.359
A neon alien…

07:01.943 --> 07:05.320
I laughed properly for the first time
thanks to her.

07:06.906 --> 07:09.074
I used to be trapped in a tiny world,

07:09.075 --> 07:12.954
and it grew wider because of her.

07:14.956 --> 07:17.375
But that person
who laughed and shone so brightly…

07:18.793 --> 07:19.878
keeps crying now.

07:21.004 --> 07:22.254
She keeps hiding.

07:23.339 --> 07:25.799
I want to do the same for her now

07:25.800 --> 07:28.762
and help her live joyfully again.

07:29.554 --> 07:33.975
Because she was a grateful disruption
that made me live again.

07:36.269 --> 07:39.981
Is it okay if I start being
really nice to you from now on?

07:45.904 --> 07:46.905
No,

07:47.614 --> 07:48.947
you can't.

07:48.948 --> 07:49.949
What?

07:50.575 --> 07:51.700
Why?

07:51.701 --> 07:52.951
Oh, right.

07:52.952 --> 07:55.205
I just want to repay you for what you did.

07:57.582 --> 08:00.335
If it's because of those clothes,
it's fine.

08:00.960 --> 08:04.130
I have no intention
of getting close to anyone.

08:08.051 --> 08:09.511
What if there's a time limit?

08:13.640 --> 08:14.766
I…

08:15.517 --> 08:17.519
I just meant…

08:18.436 --> 08:22.148
We can be friends while I'm in Korea.

08:22.899 --> 08:25.360
Just for three months.

08:33.660 --> 08:35.786
We'll keep seeing each other
at work and at SHIM.

08:35.787 --> 08:36.912
So…

08:36.913 --> 08:39.248
"Let's live so I won't have any regrets."

08:39.249 --> 08:41.041
You said that was your motto.

08:41.042 --> 08:43.837
"Let's not get close to anyone.
Then nothing will happen."

08:44.379 --> 08:45.964
That's my motto.

08:46.798 --> 08:51.093
I'll get along with you very well
as a colleague.

08:51.094 --> 08:54.430
But I will never get close
to you personally.

09:02.021 --> 09:03.438
A three-month trial!

09:05.191 --> 09:07.193
You know, like free trials
in apps and games.

09:07.861 --> 09:09.279
There's nothing to lose.

09:10.155 --> 09:12.114
You can use me as a friend
when you're bored

09:12.115 --> 09:13.950
or a misunderstanding for Ms. Kim.

09:14.450 --> 09:16.035
Just try me out as a free trial.

09:16.786 --> 09:21.291
As soon as the three months is over,
I'll disappear without a trace.

09:23.960 --> 09:25.712
All right, fine.

09:27.797 --> 09:29.756
You really don't want to be friends?

09:29.757 --> 09:31.384
No.

09:32.886 --> 09:35.680
Okay. I understand.

09:36.306 --> 09:38.975
Then, I'll make you want
to become my friend.

09:40.018 --> 09:41.310
- Excuse me?
- Mmm.

09:43.938 --> 09:45.356
I hope you get better soon.

09:47.609 --> 09:48.610
What…

10:07.378 --> 10:10.548
HERBAL TEA

11:21.369 --> 11:23.496
IN YOUR RADIANT SEASON

11:24.038 --> 11:25.122
Haran.

11:32.255 --> 11:34.756
Geez. Are you a bear?

11:34.757 --> 11:36.509
You're sleeping in the cave now?

11:37.135 --> 11:39.554
I fell asleep.

11:40.388 --> 11:42.597
Come downstairs.

11:42.598 --> 11:44.142
I have something to announce.

11:45.893 --> 11:49.896
First of all, thank you
for gathering early in the morning.

11:49.897 --> 11:53.191
Please understand,
since I'm a busy high school senior.

11:53.192 --> 11:55.194
I'm sleepy. Just get to the point, please.

11:56.863 --> 11:58.323
Okay, I will.

12:00.700 --> 12:01.826
I'm going to get married.

12:03.202 --> 12:08.832
Mmm. You're always planning things,
but aren't you planning way too far ahead?

12:08.833 --> 12:12.962
No, I want to get married in a few months.

12:15.423 --> 12:17.549
- With whom?
- My boyfriend.

12:17.550 --> 12:20.720
What do you mean?
How can you just get married…

12:23.473 --> 12:24.723
Wait a minute.

12:24.724 --> 12:28.018
I trust you,
but this is really sudden,

12:28.019 --> 12:30.437
so I'm asking just in case.

12:30.438 --> 12:33.315
- Are you…
- Don't be ridiculous.

12:33.316 --> 12:36.651
We've been dating purely
without crossing the line.

12:36.652 --> 12:38.445
Don't even think about it.

12:38.446 --> 12:40.781
Tell me. Who is he?

12:40.782 --> 12:42.991
I've known him since elementary school.

12:42.992 --> 12:45.994
Cha Yougyum.
He's in our school's baseball team.

12:45.995 --> 12:50.416
He should focus on baseball
instead of seducing our innocent Hadam.

12:51.042 --> 12:54.169
He's an innocent guy
who only thinks about baseball and me.

12:54.170 --> 12:55.921
I'm the one who suggested marriage.

12:55.922 --> 12:59.716
Fine, let's say you get married.
How will you make a living?

12:59.717 --> 13:02.761
He's joining the Major League.
He's joining the New York Comets.

13:02.762 --> 13:03.846
It was on the news.

13:04.430 --> 13:05.722
The Comets?

13:05.723 --> 13:09.434
So are you saying
you'll give up your studies

13:09.435 --> 13:11.645
and go to the US with him?

13:11.646 --> 13:15.607
No, I'm going to medical school here
like I planned.

13:15.608 --> 13:19.653
I want us to get married
so I won't feel anxious when he's away.

13:19.654 --> 13:21.571
Things won't change much right away.

13:21.572 --> 13:24.533
She planned everything already.

13:24.534 --> 13:25.784
Hey, Hadam.

13:25.785 --> 13:28.161
You don't know much about life yet, so--

13:28.162 --> 13:29.830
Wait.

13:29.831 --> 13:31.248
Let me meet him first.

13:31.249 --> 13:33.418
Grandma!

13:34.419 --> 13:35.544
All right.

13:35.545 --> 13:38.755
He's in Jeju Island for a competition,
so I'll bring him home after.

13:38.756 --> 13:42.385
Okay. We'll discuss this after I meet him.

13:48.015 --> 13:51.477
I have to go study now,
so I'll see you later.

13:52.311 --> 13:53.396
Song Hadam.

13:54.647 --> 13:56.940
Hey. How…

13:56.941 --> 13:59.569
Haran. Sis!

14:00.403 --> 14:03.613
Shouldn't you say something
as the eldest sister?

14:03.614 --> 14:06.033
Grandma said she'll discuss it
after meeting him.

14:06.534 --> 14:07.660
Go get ready for work.

14:08.244 --> 14:09.245
What?

14:10.580 --> 14:12.205
How are they all so relaxed

14:12.206 --> 14:14.375
when a teenager said
she's getting married?

14:15.710 --> 14:18.129
Mom, Dad. Isn't this crazy?

14:29.724 --> 14:32.934
Then, I'll make you want
to become my friend.

14:32.935 --> 14:34.978
I'll make you want
to become my friend.

14:36.731 --> 14:38.608
What is he trying to do?

14:42.111 --> 14:43.404
Do you have a meeting here?

14:44.113 --> 14:46.865
No, I just wanted to get everyone coffee.

14:46.866 --> 14:48.408
Coffee? Nice!

14:48.409 --> 14:50.119
I'll be back in a second.

14:53.581 --> 14:56.292
Oh. Ms. Song, what are you doing?

14:56.959 --> 14:59.295
It's nothing.

15:04.967 --> 15:07.594
Mmm.

15:07.595 --> 15:08.638
This is good.

15:12.642 --> 15:14.142
Where's Ms. Song?

15:14.143 --> 15:16.354
She disappears at 12 on the dot.

15:17.063 --> 15:20.023
Is she Lunch Cinderella or what?
Where is she even going?

15:20.024 --> 15:22.193
Does she think I'll get curious about her?

15:23.194 --> 15:25.487
Since you're here, have lunch with us.

15:25.488 --> 15:27.072
Sorry, I'll pass today.

15:27.073 --> 15:28.991
Next time. Enjoy your lunch.

15:31.494 --> 15:32.744
Genius.

15:32.745 --> 15:35.747
Are you visiting, too?

15:35.748 --> 15:36.832
Aww.

15:38.417 --> 15:40.460
I can't go to SHIM for a while.

15:40.461 --> 15:42.087
I'll see you later.

16:05.569 --> 16:06.570
Ugh...

16:27.842 --> 16:30.343
No way.

16:37.310 --> 16:38.476
I'm sorry.

16:38.477 --> 16:42.064
Are you okay?
I'll order the same one for you.

16:45.526 --> 16:48.321
Okay. Let's run the meeting
with Lafayette like this.

16:49.030 --> 16:50.739
Is there anything else? If that's it…

16:50.740 --> 16:52.658
I want to say something.

16:53.326 --> 16:54.535
Go on.

16:55.703 --> 17:00.457
I want to be excluded
from the animation collaboration.

17:06.172 --> 17:07.256
Why?

17:08.090 --> 17:11.885
Well, I don't know much about animation,

17:11.886 --> 17:13.970
and I don't think I'm skilled enough--

17:13.971 --> 17:15.014
Stop.

17:15.639 --> 17:16.891
That's a long excuse.

17:18.434 --> 17:19.726
Prove yourself instead.

17:19.727 --> 17:20.895
Just do it, no matter what.

17:22.938 --> 17:23.939
That's it for today.

17:25.399 --> 17:28.402
Thank you.

17:46.962 --> 17:48.839
Mr. Park. Oh…

17:50.174 --> 17:51.508
Is she not here?

17:51.509 --> 17:53.593
Do you need to see her?

17:53.594 --> 17:55.804
It's nothing.
I'll head upstairs.

17:55.805 --> 17:57.098
All right.

18:05.648 --> 18:06.815
Ah.

18:06.816 --> 18:09.109
- I'm heading out for a bit!
- Okay.

18:10.820 --> 18:13.405
He just got here. Where is he going?

18:13.406 --> 18:15.616
Mr. Park, I'm going upstairs!

18:17.410 --> 18:19.119
Mr. Park, I'm heading out!

18:19.120 --> 18:21.204
- Where are you going?
- Just buying something!

18:21.205 --> 18:23.540
- Good boy. Wait.
-  I'm going upstairs!

18:25.876 --> 18:27.836
-  Is it broken?
- Did you break something?

18:27.837 --> 18:31.132
No, it's fine.
I'm going upstairs.

18:33.968 --> 18:38.013
Genius, do you know why he's so busy?

19:01.537 --> 19:03.581
- Yes, this is Nana Atelier--
-  Help me.

19:04.081 --> 19:05.498
Hayeong?

19:05.499 --> 19:07.334
It's 39,000 won.

19:11.547 --> 19:14.007
I'll transfer the money.
It's fine.

19:14.008 --> 19:16.177
It's okay. Eat as much as you want.

19:17.803 --> 19:18.887
Here.

19:18.888 --> 19:20.096
YUMMY SNACK BAR

19:20.097 --> 19:21.222
Okay.

19:21.223 --> 19:22.683
Then I'll treat you next time.

19:25.978 --> 19:27.896
Here. Have one.

19:27.897 --> 19:30.440
- It's fine--
- Come on. Try it.

19:30.441 --> 19:32.984
I mean, no one carries around
cash these days.

19:32.985 --> 19:34.987
I was about to transfer the money,

19:35.696 --> 19:39.658
but I left my phone
at the office.

19:40.409 --> 19:43.203
So I borrowed the owner's phone
and called,

19:43.204 --> 19:47.040
hoping someone would pick up at work.

19:47.041 --> 19:49.834
And, wow, the man
who always goes home last

19:49.835 --> 19:51.836
picked up and saved me.

19:51.837 --> 19:54.172
Applause.

19:54.173 --> 19:55.299
Hang on.

19:57.134 --> 19:58.385
Hey, Chaewon.

19:58.886 --> 19:59.887
A blind date?

20:00.721 --> 20:02.473
Okay, send me his profile.

20:03.307 --> 20:04.433
Okay.

20:07.228 --> 20:08.394
Someone saw my photo

20:08.395 --> 20:10.438
and asked my friend
to set us up on a date.

20:10.439 --> 20:11.857
He said I'm his type.

20:14.360 --> 20:17.238
I always end up just being friends
with guys on blind dates.

20:19.573 --> 20:22.910
But this time, it might be different.

20:23.619 --> 20:24.662
He's handsome, right?

20:25.204 --> 20:28.916
"Cha Min."
Even his name is nice.

20:29.792 --> 20:31.210
What do you think, Mr. Yeon?

20:32.962 --> 20:34.838
I'm not so sure.

20:34.839 --> 20:36.882
You're not so sure?

20:37.508 --> 20:39.176
Mmm. He looks okay.

20:39.969 --> 20:42.304
Thank you.

20:43.264 --> 20:44.681
Bye!

20:44.682 --> 20:46.933
-  Come again next time!
-  Okay.

20:46.934 --> 20:48.310
Right, my phone!

20:51.438 --> 20:52.773
Bye!

21:05.870 --> 21:07.997
CHARACTER "WON"

21:11.166 --> 21:15.462
I want to be excluded
from the animation collaboration.

21:18.424 --> 21:20.050
Did they argue?

21:22.636 --> 21:23.637
Hang on.

21:24.889 --> 21:25.931
No…

21:29.476 --> 21:32.146
I'm going on a blind date.

21:32.938 --> 21:33.939
Okay.

21:34.690 --> 21:37.108
Were you two deceiving me?

21:37.109 --> 21:38.485
What?

21:39.403 --> 21:42.281
You're seeing someone,
but you're at home on a weekend?

21:44.408 --> 21:45.992
You were lying to me, weren't you?

21:45.993 --> 21:47.535
We weren't lying.

21:47.536 --> 21:50.163
Didn't you say you were meeting him today?

21:50.164 --> 21:51.331
What?

21:51.332 --> 21:55.461
I… Gosh, it's time to go.
We can head out together.

21:56.837 --> 21:58.380
See you later.

21:58.923 --> 21:59.924
Bye!

22:04.678 --> 22:06.472
That's suspicious.

22:07.932 --> 22:09.224
Is it really true?

22:13.854 --> 22:16.189
Hayeong, why do you keep doing this?

22:16.190 --> 22:19.108
Shh! This is for your sake.

22:19.109 --> 22:21.527
Mr. Yoon won't be
the only one on Grandma's list.

22:21.528 --> 22:23.404
Just spend some time outside.

22:23.405 --> 22:25.406
You can go to Genius' coffee shop.

22:25.407 --> 22:26.951
I can't go there.

22:27.576 --> 22:29.619
- Maybe I should go to the office.
- No.

22:29.620 --> 22:31.621
Don't you know Grandma?

22:31.622 --> 22:33.790
I bet she checks all the entrance records.

22:34.875 --> 22:37.210
Hang in there, okay?

22:37.211 --> 22:38.628
Bye!

22:38.629 --> 22:39.922
Mr. Cha? Hi.

22:41.215 --> 22:42.925
Darn it.

22:44.426 --> 22:45.803
I have nowhere to go.

22:53.978 --> 22:56.855
The course was so tough today.

22:59.483 --> 23:00.776
Gosh.

23:02.361 --> 23:03.570
There's a large variety.

23:05.322 --> 23:08.741
Then I'll make you want
to become my friend.

23:08.742 --> 23:12.495
I'll make you want
to become my friend.

23:12.496 --> 23:13.872
Geez.

23:14.915 --> 23:18.501
You ran around a lot today,
so this is on me today.

23:18.502 --> 23:21.045
So have anything you want.

23:21.046 --> 23:22.755
I'm going to have
something expensive.

23:22.756 --> 23:23.966
Who are you?

23:24.550 --> 23:26.093
What? I…

23:26.510 --> 23:29.013
Ah.  I have a girlfriend.

23:30.597 --> 23:33.641
No, it's not that.
Sorry. I'll just sit here for a second.

23:33.642 --> 23:35.977
You were amazing, Mr. Seonu.

23:35.978 --> 23:37.645
How were you so good on your first day?

23:37.646 --> 23:42.400
I was just doing my best
not to fall behind.

23:42.401 --> 23:45.403
Number 26, your order's ready.

23:47.406 --> 23:49.157
You can have this.

23:49.158 --> 23:52.118
Number 26, your salad is ready.

23:52.119 --> 23:53.537
Number 26?

23:54.872 --> 23:58.166
Number 26, your order is ready.

23:58.167 --> 23:59.877
Number 26?

24:24.526 --> 24:26.152
It's only 5:00 p.m.

24:26.153 --> 24:27.196
Tsk.

24:28.197 --> 24:30.239
You're good!

24:31.950 --> 24:33.785
You're so good!

24:33.786 --> 24:34.912
- Right?
-  You're amazing!

24:36.246 --> 24:39.415
Then I'll make you want
to become my friend.

24:39.416 --> 24:41.084
I'll make you want
to become my friend.

24:43.462 --> 24:44.754
What is he doing here?

24:44.755 --> 24:46.047
I want to do it, too.

24:46.048 --> 24:47.799
-  You're so good.
-  I want to do it.

24:47.800 --> 24:49.843
I want to do it, too!

24:53.806 --> 24:55.515
- Oh no.
- Oh no.

24:55.516 --> 24:56.850
I'm sorry!

25:00.813 --> 25:02.231
Where do I go?

25:06.568 --> 25:08.570
Where did she go?

25:09.154 --> 25:10.280
I'm sorry!

25:43.021 --> 25:46.607
Then, I'll make you want
to become my friend.

25:46.608 --> 25:48.402
Again?

25:52.489 --> 25:55.200
Oh? Ms. Song!

25:59.163 --> 26:00.788
It's nice being neighbors.

26:00.789 --> 26:03.667
I was going to call you to give you this.

26:04.251 --> 26:06.002
Aren't they pretty?

26:06.003 --> 26:08.379
Green tangerine, lemon, beet…

26:08.380 --> 26:10.590
They're good for…
Hey, you're not coughing.

26:10.591 --> 26:13.302
I'm sorry, but I have to go…

26:14.052 --> 26:15.846
I have to go. Sorry.

26:29.109 --> 26:30.651
Watch the traffic lights!

26:32.029 --> 26:33.030
Are you okay?

26:33.864 --> 26:36.366
Uh… Why were you in such a hurry?

26:38.368 --> 26:39.619
Are you hurt?

26:39.620 --> 26:40.787
Let me see.

26:43.040 --> 26:44.750
Wait.

26:51.298 --> 26:53.800
Sorry, sir.

26:56.345 --> 26:57.845
We should go to a hospital.

26:57.846 --> 26:59.181
It's fine.

26:59.848 --> 27:02.935
No, it's not. You hurt your hand,
and you're a designer.

27:06.188 --> 27:08.106
I'm sorry.

27:09.024 --> 27:11.151
- Let's go get you treated.
- Why did you…

27:14.655 --> 27:17.407
I told you I have no intention
of getting close to you.

27:18.158 --> 27:22.536
It makes me uncomfortable
when you act like we're close.

27:22.537 --> 27:27.249
It may have sounded weird since I'm a guy,
but I didn't mean anything like that--

27:27.250 --> 27:30.169
Whether you're a guy or not,
I don't want to get close.

27:30.170 --> 27:33.715
I can't even go to the cafe
I love the most because of you, and…

27:36.802 --> 27:39.345
I can't keep avoiding you
in the same neighborhood,

27:39.346 --> 27:40.930
so let me be frank.

27:40.931 --> 27:42.516
I'm really sorry,

27:43.892 --> 27:46.019
but I'm a bit weird.

27:46.770 --> 27:49.356
I feel at ease
only if nothing happens in my life.

27:50.190 --> 27:52.358
I hate people entering my life,

27:52.359 --> 27:54.527
and I hate my daily routine
getting disturbed.

27:54.528 --> 27:55.611
I…

27:55.612 --> 27:58.156
I don't need any variables in my life.

27:59.116 --> 28:00.200
Please.

28:07.457 --> 28:10.042
I understand. I get it.

28:10.043 --> 28:13.213
I'll just stand quietly next to you,

28:15.257 --> 28:16.550
so let's go to the hospital.

28:18.135 --> 28:19.386
Your wrist's swollen.

28:22.848 --> 28:24.224
Please.

28:33.984 --> 28:35.985
Uh… It's a Grade 1 sprain.

28:35.986 --> 28:38.487
There's some irritation
to the soft tissue,

28:38.488 --> 28:41.575
so try not to move your wrist too much
for the next two weeks.

28:42.659 --> 28:44.035
The nurse will treat you.

28:44.036 --> 28:45.536
All right. Thank you.

28:45.537 --> 28:47.371
- Just a moment, please.
- Okay.

28:47.372 --> 28:48.415
Thank you.

29:01.887 --> 29:04.263
Come out when you're done.

29:04.264 --> 29:05.474
I'll be waiting outside.

29:12.647 --> 29:16.317
Do I have to keep this on?
My family's going to worry.

29:16.318 --> 29:19.403
You can switch to a brace
and take it off from time to time.

29:19.404 --> 29:22.156
Wearing it for too long
will slow down natural healing,

29:22.157 --> 29:25.534
so check your condition for a few days
and take it off if there's no pain.

29:25.535 --> 29:26.703
Okay.

29:48.558 --> 29:51.727
Number 26, your salad is ready.

29:51.728 --> 29:55.023
I can't even go to the cafe
I love the most because of you, and…

30:33.979 --> 30:35.397
I'm sorry.

30:38.900 --> 30:42.195
I didn't think what I said
bothered you that much.

30:43.488 --> 30:45.282
If I was an uncomfortable variable,

30:46.825 --> 30:47.868
I'm really sorry.

30:48.827 --> 30:49.828
Oh…

30:50.662 --> 30:53.456
So just come to SHIM whenever you want.

30:54.040 --> 30:56.251
It would be a shame
not to be able to go there.

30:56.835 --> 30:58.002
I'll move out.

30:58.003 --> 31:00.296
And walk around the neighborhood
as you want.

31:00.297 --> 31:03.507
I'll leave so we won't
run into each other.

31:03.508 --> 31:05.009
Just give me a few days.

31:05.010 --> 31:06.011
And at work,

31:06.803 --> 31:08.805
I'll pretend nothing happened.

31:09.890 --> 31:11.308
I promise to never create

31:13.185 --> 31:14.477
any variables for you…

31:17.063 --> 31:19.024
or bother you again.

31:20.609 --> 31:22.485
I…

31:23.737 --> 31:26.781
Oh. Sorry, sir. She's getting in.

31:29.910 --> 31:30.993
Go on.

32:08.323 --> 32:10.450
SHIM

32:11.284 --> 32:12.285
Hmm?

32:16.289 --> 32:18.332
Mr. Park, hi.

32:18.333 --> 32:19.334
Hey there.

32:19.960 --> 32:21.794
Sorry for calling you.

32:21.795 --> 32:24.588
You've been coming here every day
for seven years,

32:24.589 --> 32:27.341
so I've been worried
since you haven't come in a while.

32:27.342 --> 32:28.884
Are you sick or anything?

32:28.885 --> 32:30.720
I'm just busy with work.

32:31.221 --> 32:32.931
I'll be back once it's settled.

32:34.099 --> 32:35.183
Yes.

32:36.184 --> 32:37.393
I'm here!

32:37.394 --> 32:38.602
You're late.

32:38.603 --> 32:39.895
You had dinner, right?

32:39.896 --> 32:42.815
Of course.
I enjoyed the stew you cooked for me.

32:42.816 --> 32:45.527
How are you such a good cook?

32:46.444 --> 32:48.071
What about your medicine?

32:53.618 --> 32:56.328
I thought I'd feel safer
if there was someone with me.

32:56.329 --> 32:59.248
And he's adorable.

32:59.249 --> 33:01.542
He's a really good man.

33:01.543 --> 33:03.211
I'll move out.

33:12.387 --> 33:14.513
Of course, I took my medicine.

33:14.514 --> 33:17.975
I get a harsh scolding
from someone named Chan

33:17.976 --> 33:20.269
if I don't take them.

33:23.356 --> 33:24.357
Oh?

33:26.109 --> 33:28.820
This guy must be
going through a transplant shock.

33:29.821 --> 33:31.405
A transplant shock?

33:31.406 --> 33:34.408
When plants are suddenly
put in a different environment…

33:34.409 --> 33:38.287
they go into shock,
thinking, "Where am I"?

33:38.288 --> 33:39.289
Just like humans.

33:40.290 --> 33:44.961
They need time to adjust
to an unexpected variable.

33:45.545 --> 33:47.047
A variable…

33:48.423 --> 33:52.844
What if… they can't adjust?

33:53.720 --> 33:56.181
A lot of them just wither

33:57.098 --> 33:58.641
and die in the end.

33:59.893 --> 34:02.812
It's a pity.

34:05.106 --> 34:07.609
I should clean up.

34:08.276 --> 34:10.444
Wait, I'll do it.

34:10.445 --> 34:14.698
I said I'd kick you out if you do this.
It's my job to do that.

34:14.699 --> 34:18.703
I love cleaning windows.
It's a habit of mine.

34:19.454 --> 34:20.622
My gosh.

34:24.167 --> 34:25.377
All right…

34:30.715 --> 34:33.926
I can't even go to the cafe
I love the most because of you, and…

34:33.927 --> 34:36.596
Come to SHIM whenever you want.
I'll move out.

34:37.222 --> 34:38.514
Mr. Park.

34:38.515 --> 34:40.891
How can you be so adorable?

34:40.892 --> 34:44.896
I feel like I've suddenly gotten a son.

34:46.481 --> 34:48.525
Thank you for being here.

34:53.405 --> 34:54.572
Oh, right.

34:56.032 --> 34:59.536
Weren't you about to say something to me?

35:00.537 --> 35:01.538
I…

35:02.997 --> 35:07.585
I'll clean up here,
so you can go to bed.

35:08.712 --> 35:09.754
All right.

35:11.005 --> 35:12.006
And…

35:13.967 --> 35:15.300
sleep tight.

35:17.387 --> 35:18.554
Okay.

35:18.555 --> 35:20.055
- Good night.
- Good night.

35:20.056 --> 35:21.182
Oh, my.

35:22.892 --> 35:25.145
Tsk.

35:26.062 --> 35:28.064
Tsk.

35:28.565 --> 35:33.486
cafe SHIM

35:38.700 --> 35:39.701
Tsk.

35:49.878 --> 35:52.422
I should have just left her be.

35:53.548 --> 35:54.924
It wasn't my business.

36:03.975 --> 36:05.267
Good work, everyone.

36:05.268 --> 36:06.810
Go, Cheongsol!

36:06.811 --> 36:08.729
Go, Cheongsol!

36:08.730 --> 36:10.564
-  Great work.
-  Great job.

36:10.565 --> 36:11.857
Great job, everyone.

36:14.027 --> 36:15.652
Why are you taking off your pants?

36:15.653 --> 36:17.030
Take my uniform.

36:19.240 --> 36:21.408
Cha Yougyum!
Where are you going?

36:21.409 --> 36:23.203
I'm going to see Hadam!

36:29.250 --> 36:31.543
Hey, Hadam.
I'll be there in three minutes.

36:31.544 --> 36:33.671
It's a green light!

36:34.547 --> 36:37.382
Don't run. I'm still on my way.

36:37.383 --> 36:40.552
LAUNDRY DETERGENT, WHITE MUSK

36:42.764 --> 36:44.431
What is it? Yougyum.

36:47.393 --> 36:48.561
Cha Yougyum!

37:03.952 --> 37:06.286
Hadam!

37:06.287 --> 37:07.372
Song Hadam!

37:15.672 --> 37:17.798
What's wrong, Hadam?

37:17.799 --> 37:21.385
I heard a thud over the phone…

37:21.386 --> 37:24.973
Oh… Sorry. Someone was in danger,
so I had to help them.

37:27.725 --> 37:29.561
It's fine if you're okay.

37:30.311 --> 37:32.062
Is that person okay?

37:32.063 --> 37:33.481
Yes, thankfully.

37:34.065 --> 37:36.734
I promise not to worry you again.
I'm really sorry.

37:37.360 --> 37:39.361
You must have been angry.

37:39.362 --> 37:41.906
No, I like you even more now.

37:43.032 --> 37:44.908
You're so kind.

37:44.909 --> 37:46.743
Grandma told me to bring you home.

37:46.744 --> 37:48.161
Hmm?

37:50.290 --> 37:52.499
My heart's going to explode already.

37:52.500 --> 37:55.252
What do I wear? A suit?
Our school uniform?

37:55.253 --> 37:57.421
Not my baseball uniform.
Should I do my hair?

37:57.422 --> 37:59.506
I should get new socks, and…

37:59.507 --> 38:02.050
First, let's eat something.

38:02.051 --> 38:04.887
I'm hungry
after all that running.

38:04.888 --> 38:06.556
Okay.

38:11.060 --> 38:12.061
Ah.

38:12.645 --> 38:15.857
But do you really think
we can get married before I go?

38:16.649 --> 38:20.320
Yougyum, did you ever see me
failing to carry out a plan?

38:21.029 --> 38:23.114
- No.
- We just have to stick to my plan.

38:24.908 --> 38:26.033
You're so cool.

38:28.786 --> 38:30.621
The game was tough, wasn't it?

38:30.622 --> 38:32.623
It wasn't that tough,

38:32.624 --> 38:35.459
but I feel like I aged 10 years
from missing you so much.

38:35.460 --> 38:37.462
I aged 20 years.

38:44.052 --> 38:45.595
Here. Hang on.

38:47.180 --> 38:48.305
Wait.

38:51.809 --> 38:55.688
Now, this drawing…
will turn into real candy.

38:58.024 --> 39:01.068
- No way.
- That's nonsense.

39:01.069 --> 39:02.361
I mean it.

39:02.362 --> 39:03.988
All right… Mmm.

39:09.452 --> 39:11.078
Look.

39:11.079 --> 39:13.664
- Where did they come from?
- What was that?

39:13.665 --> 39:15.499
They're real.

39:15.500 --> 39:16.792
They're real candy.

39:16.793 --> 39:18.543
Take them. Take them.

39:22.048 --> 39:23.340
These actually are real.

39:23.341 --> 39:25.009
-  How did you do that?
-  Unbelievable.

39:25.134 --> 39:26.135
Hi.

39:30.390 --> 39:32.224
This is some kind of trick, right?

39:32.225 --> 39:35.310
Chan, tell me how you did it.
I want to show my friends.

39:35.311 --> 39:36.728
-  Okay.
- "Chan"?

39:36.729 --> 39:38.480
I'll send a video to our group chat.

39:38.481 --> 39:40.315
Yes!

39:40.316 --> 39:42.442
Right, Chan. We need a revenge match.

39:42.443 --> 39:44.236
- "Group chat"?
-  Let's go bowling again.

39:44.237 --> 39:45.821
Sure. Anytime.

39:45.822 --> 39:47.907
- I want to join, too!
- Me too. Me too.

39:50.910 --> 39:52.869
-  Are you sure?
-  This will be fun.

39:52.870 --> 39:54.538
How will we divide teams?

39:54.539 --> 39:56.123
-  Our teams?
-  Well…

39:56.124 --> 39:57.332
♪ Flip your hands ♪

39:57.333 --> 39:59.459
-  What?
-  What is that?

39:59.460 --> 40:02.546
Let's be friends while I'm in Korea.
Can I be really nice to you?

40:02.547 --> 40:04.381
Sure. Of course.

40:04.382 --> 40:05.674
Of course.

40:05.675 --> 40:08.385
I really wanted to get close to you.

40:08.386 --> 40:10.388
- Sure.
- Yes, sure. I'd love that.

40:11.889 --> 40:14.683
No, you can't.

40:14.684 --> 40:17.019
Whether it's a guy or not,

40:17.020 --> 40:19.439
I have no intention
of getting close to anyone.

40:20.940 --> 40:23.108
Rock, paper…

40:23.109 --> 40:24.359
Okay, rock.

40:24.360 --> 40:25.527
- One, two, three.
-  Okay!

40:27.989 --> 40:29.698
-  This is a revenge match.
-  We won.

40:40.710 --> 40:46.466
Did I overreact
when he asked everyone to be friends?

40:52.096 --> 40:56.224
Then let's select some
dancheong references that will suit Won

40:56.225 --> 40:58.227
and put together a few rough drafts.

40:58.770 --> 40:59.853
Sure.

40:59.854 --> 41:02.647
I'm visiting some palaces
for some research tomorrow.

41:02.648 --> 41:04.066
I'll take a lot of photos.

41:04.067 --> 41:05.651
- Really?
- Yes.

41:07.320 --> 41:08.780
You're going too, right?

41:09.864 --> 41:11.907
- Me?
- Yes, you.

41:11.908 --> 41:14.701
Shouldn't you do something
to show me results?

41:14.702 --> 41:17.537
Well, I have a fabric meeting tomorrow,

41:17.538 --> 41:19.499
- and I have to go to the factory--
- Send Raemee.

41:21.584 --> 41:23.044
Go with him. It's for work.

41:24.462 --> 41:27.047
You can bring Ms. Song with you, right?

41:27.048 --> 41:28.758
Well…

41:29.342 --> 41:33.261
Then can I go to the palaces instead?
Ms. Song can go to the factory…

41:36.766 --> 41:39.267
I would love to go to the factory.

41:39.268 --> 41:42.855
I'll go there, and Ms. Song can go
to the palaces.

41:43.397 --> 41:46.526
Okay. Then let's gather
at our next meeting.

41:47.693 --> 41:50.947
Ms. Kim, when should I go
to the factory tomorrow?

41:54.617 --> 41:56.910
If you feel uneasy,
I'll go on a different date.

41:56.911 --> 41:58.036
You can tell Ms. Kim--

41:58.037 --> 42:01.082
No, let's go. It's for work.

42:04.252 --> 42:05.920
Right. It's for work.

42:06.671 --> 42:08.381
Then I'll text you the details.

42:09.340 --> 42:12.634
And I'm sorry,
but give me some time to move out.

42:12.635 --> 42:14.387
I haven't told Mr. Park yet.

42:15.304 --> 42:16.847
Then I'll see you tomorrow.

42:16.848 --> 42:18.099
I…

42:30.736 --> 42:33.864
Yes. I'm heading to the Lafayette meeting.

42:33.865 --> 42:35.448
I'll call you after.

42:35.449 --> 42:37.909
-  Oh, gosh!
-  What? What is it?

42:37.910 --> 42:38.994
Oh, my gosh!

42:38.995 --> 42:41.163
-  What is it?
-  What's with those flowers?

42:41.164 --> 42:42.414
I received them.

42:42.415 --> 42:43.498
What?

42:43.499 --> 42:46.668
Your date treated you to lunch
and gave you flowers?

42:46.669 --> 42:49.546
Hang on, aren't these ranunculus flowers?

42:49.547 --> 42:51.882
They mean "You're beautiful."

42:51.883 --> 42:54.426
Am I beautiful?

42:54.427 --> 42:56.928
Geez. What's with you?

42:56.929 --> 42:58.722
Are you dating? It doesn't suit you.

42:58.723 --> 43:01.559
Not yet, but we'll meet often.
His workplace is nearby.

43:02.185 --> 43:05.228
So I won't be able to have lunch
with you guys for a while.

43:06.314 --> 43:08.274
-  I'm so jealous.
-  Congratulations!

43:09.108 --> 43:10.942
-  When are you meeting again?
-  Tomorrow.

43:12.028 --> 43:14.238
-  No way.
-  I'm so jealous.

43:15.781 --> 43:17.365
Just to confirm,

43:17.366 --> 43:21.536
do you want to tweak the details
on the Lafayette coat line one more time?

43:21.537 --> 43:25.333
Yes. If you don't mind, we'd appreciate
pushing the delivery back a bit.

43:26.209 --> 43:27.584
I got a boyfriend.

43:27.585 --> 43:29.002
- What do you think?
- Let me see.

43:29.003 --> 43:30.754
- He's so handsome.
- Isn't he?

43:30.755 --> 43:32.672
- What does he do?
-  Let me see. Oh, my gosh.

43:34.217 --> 43:35.259
Hello.

43:35.927 --> 43:39.930
Do you know the meaning
of these ranunculus flowers?

43:39.931 --> 43:41.431
I don't know.

43:41.432 --> 43:42.933
"You're beautiful."

43:42.934 --> 43:44.059
What?

43:44.060 --> 43:45.143
Thank you.

43:46.229 --> 43:48.606
You said you couldn't come today.

43:50.858 --> 43:53.027
Surprise.

43:55.112 --> 43:58.699
He's handsome, right?
"Cha Min." Even his name is nice.

43:59.992 --> 44:01.785
I got these for you.

44:01.786 --> 44:03.788
- What?
- Did you eat?

44:05.122 --> 44:08.250
Mr. Yeon,
would one more week be okay with you?

44:08.251 --> 44:10.670
Oh, yes.

44:12.380 --> 44:13.838
Would you like some coffee?

44:16.133 --> 44:17.760
Thank you.

44:19.428 --> 44:21.847
Hey, you look nice.

44:23.099 --> 44:25.058
It's been a while
since I wore a hanbok.

44:25.059 --> 44:26.142
SINGPUNGNU

44:26.143 --> 44:27.395
Wow, it's so cool.

44:29.605 --> 44:31.941
This is going to be awkward.

44:43.119 --> 44:44.787
You've got to be kidding me.

44:48.916 --> 44:50.376
You're here.

44:51.669 --> 44:53.462
Your outfit…

44:54.422 --> 44:56.673
Ah. The fee is free if we wear a hanbok.

44:56.674 --> 44:58.717
If you want,
there's a rental shop over there…

44:58.718 --> 45:00.594
No, it's completely fine.

45:01.429 --> 45:02.430
All right.

45:03.180 --> 45:04.807
- Let's go, then.
- Okay.

45:36.630 --> 45:38.632
Wow. Aren't they beautiful?

45:39.842 --> 45:41.343
Thanks to the dancheong,

45:41.344 --> 45:44.180
the wood doesn't rot in the rain
and is protected from pests.

45:45.681 --> 45:46.724
Isn't it awesome?

45:47.433 --> 45:48.434
Mmm.

45:49.018 --> 45:50.436
It's just basic knowledge.

45:51.062 --> 45:53.980
I'd like to brag,
but I studied that in advance.

45:53.981 --> 45:55.775
I like showing off my knowledge.

46:00.905 --> 46:02.906
This is my bucket list for Korea.

46:02.907 --> 46:05.201
I'd feel upset if I didn't do all these.

46:06.660 --> 46:10.622
I don't know whether I'll be back
in a decade or two,

46:10.623 --> 46:14.460
or maybe never again.

46:17.004 --> 46:20.173
Wow, hanbok looks so cool.
Can I take a picture?

46:20.174 --> 46:21.549
Of course, why not?

46:21.550 --> 46:22.718
Okay. Guys, come on.

46:24.095 --> 46:25.512
- Okay.
- Kimchi.

46:25.513 --> 46:26.764
Kimchi.

46:27.264 --> 46:28.723
- Thank you.
- Thank you so much.

46:28.724 --> 46:29.934
Have a great day.

46:30.768 --> 46:32.268
Wow, man, it looks good.

46:32.269 --> 46:34.730
Can we take a photo with you, too?

46:35.314 --> 46:36.482
One, two, three.

46:37.066 --> 46:38.942
Thank you.

46:38.943 --> 46:40.860
-  Thank you.
- Thank you. Thank you so much.

46:40.861 --> 46:42.362
-  Have a nice day.
- You too.

46:42.363 --> 46:43.364
Bye.

46:44.156 --> 46:46.574
Ah, sorry,
I wore this to break the ice,

46:46.575 --> 46:48.160
but I didn't expect this.

46:48.953 --> 46:51.330
My clothes are in the locker,
so I'll get changed.

46:53.999 --> 46:55.375
It's the king!

46:57.920 --> 46:59.547
Ice breaking…

47:11.392 --> 47:12.435
Ran!

47:21.777 --> 47:22.861
Huh?

47:22.862 --> 47:26.574
BONGSUDANG

47:27.700 --> 47:28.701
Hmm?

47:30.703 --> 47:31.704
Where did she go?

47:32.788 --> 47:34.039
Did she go to the restroom?

47:55.519 --> 47:56.562
Huh?

47:57.104 --> 47:59.398
She left her phone here?

48:27.134 --> 48:28.927
Where in the world is she?

48:42.066 --> 48:43.149
What…

48:44.527 --> 48:45.694
Ms. Song!

48:53.619 --> 48:55.286
You just disappeared.

48:55.287 --> 48:56.663
What is it?

48:56.664 --> 48:58.164
Let's go. We have to work.

48:58.165 --> 49:00.124
What's wrong?

49:00.125 --> 49:01.752
- It's nothing.
- I…

49:02.545 --> 49:06.464
I know you hate others meddling,
but let me meddle just this once.

49:06.465 --> 49:09.592
What's wrong? I'm honestly worried.

49:13.180 --> 49:16.308
Then, let's sit for a moment.

49:16.934 --> 49:18.518
My legs…

49:20.271 --> 49:21.855
Let's sit for a while.

49:31.323 --> 49:32.866
I heard a voice.

49:39.290 --> 49:40.332
Ran!

49:45.254 --> 49:47.381
Someone called my name,
so I went to look.

49:48.382 --> 49:49.550
Ran!

49:54.096 --> 49:55.346
KIM RAN

49:55.347 --> 49:56.890
- I'll try it first.
- Okay.

49:57.933 --> 50:01.395
But her voice
was so similar to my mom's.

50:02.605 --> 50:04.523
Ran, come here.

50:09.653 --> 50:12.698
It sounded like
my mom was actually calling me,

50:13.782 --> 50:15.575
so I burst into tears.

50:15.576 --> 50:16.577
Mom.

50:19.496 --> 50:21.539
Ran, Ran.

50:21.540 --> 50:24.168
My mom always called me like that.

50:36.013 --> 50:38.097
-  I like this song!
-  Mmm?

50:38.098 --> 50:40.224
It's Hadam's favorite song.

50:40.225 --> 50:41.684
It is.

50:43.270 --> 50:45.271
Hadam, do you want
to say hi to your sisters?

50:45.272 --> 50:47.148
- Yes.
- Okay.

50:47.149 --> 50:48.358
Hi!

50:48.359 --> 50:51.195
-  Hi.
-  They look so excited.

51:11.131 --> 51:12.257
Mom.

51:12.800 --> 51:13.883
Dad.

51:15.052 --> 51:16.261
Dad…

51:31.860 --> 51:33.779
Dad! Dad!

51:34.446 --> 51:35.447
Dad!

51:37.616 --> 51:39.242
Mom!

51:39.243 --> 51:40.411
Mom, get up! Mom!

51:41.203 --> 51:43.872
Mom!

51:46.959 --> 51:48.001
Please!

51:48.752 --> 51:51.129
- Mom!
- Dad.

51:51.130 --> 51:52.672
Dad!

51:52.673 --> 51:54.549
Help us!

51:56.677 --> 51:59.805
They said the driver
suddenly had a cardiac arrest.

52:00.472 --> 52:02.391
Both my parents died on the spot,

52:03.183 --> 52:06.729
right in front of me.

52:09.106 --> 52:11.191
I know she wasn't calling me,

52:11.775 --> 52:13.736
and that I was mistaken,

52:15.738 --> 52:17.780
but when I heard her voice,

52:17.781 --> 52:20.951
I think I felt happy for a split second.

52:21.994 --> 52:23.996
I know that sounds strange.

52:24.538 --> 52:26.415
Well, you felt like someone you miss

52:27.249 --> 52:29.168
called your name.

52:34.798 --> 52:36.299
Chan.

52:36.300 --> 52:37.884
I love you.

52:37.885 --> 52:39.343
I love you, Chan.

52:45.142 --> 52:47.269
It's not strange at all.

52:53.233 --> 52:54.234
Ah…

52:55.611 --> 52:58.780
I guess I was showing off again.

53:01.617 --> 53:03.201
I'm sorry.

53:03.202 --> 53:04.203
What?

53:04.745 --> 53:07.205
Oh. It's fine.
I was almost done looking around.

53:07.206 --> 53:09.166
I'm really sorry

53:10.417 --> 53:12.169
for lashing out at you until now.

53:13.670 --> 53:16.048
You did nothing wrong,

53:17.591 --> 53:19.343
but I was so harsh on you.

53:20.177 --> 53:21.887
And those fruit syrups last time…

53:23.013 --> 53:24.515
I'm really sorry.

53:25.432 --> 53:28.017
No, it's all my fault.

53:28.018 --> 53:31.562
I shouldn't have said all that stuff
about being friends.

53:31.563 --> 53:32.689
I'm sorry.

53:33.232 --> 53:34.817
Look, you're doing it again.

53:35.901 --> 53:37.903
I'm the one who's weird.

53:39.029 --> 53:43.491
I keep making other people apologize
when I'm the one who's sorry.

53:43.492 --> 53:46.285
I know I'm being rude and cruel,

53:46.286 --> 53:50.290
and I want to change,
but I don't know how.

53:51.083 --> 53:54.545
Getting close to someone
is really difficult…

53:55.671 --> 53:56.713
No,

53:57.673 --> 53:59.383
it's scary for me.

54:03.887 --> 54:06.932
Losing someone you care about
without warning

54:07.683 --> 54:09.475
is already painful enough…

54:11.770 --> 54:15.607
...but it happened to me again…
so cruelly.

54:17.401 --> 54:19.319
So I run away before it happens.

54:20.988 --> 54:24.992
Because I feel like I'll crumble
if that happens again.

54:27.953 --> 54:29.872
If no one is special to me,

54:30.914 --> 54:33.125
then at least nothing bad will happen.

54:35.752 --> 54:39.631
At first, I put up walls
to protect myself,

54:40.966 --> 54:43.552
but now, I feel like
I'm trapped behind them.

54:48.932 --> 54:51.602
Darn it. I must be crazy.
What am I doing?

54:54.563 --> 54:55.897
You're so strange.

54:56.523 --> 54:57.858
Me?

54:59.776 --> 55:04.281
As soon as the three months is over,
I'll disappear without a trace.

55:05.282 --> 55:08.160
Maybe it's because you'll leave soon.

55:08.952 --> 55:09.953
Hm.

55:10.537 --> 55:11.705
Huh?

55:18.879 --> 55:20.546
That's beautiful.

55:24.718 --> 55:26.637
I should take photos.

55:28.013 --> 55:30.431
Huh? My bag.

55:30.432 --> 55:32.099
I left my bag behind.

55:32.100 --> 55:34.143
I'll go and get it…

55:34.144 --> 55:35.312
Wait. What are you doing?

55:35.896 --> 55:38.439
- What?
- Don't you need your bag, too?

55:39.524 --> 55:41.485
My bag! Oh, gosh!

55:42.069 --> 55:43.654
Come on.

55:54.331 --> 55:55.791
I also just got off work.

55:57.417 --> 55:58.876
Oh.

55:58.877 --> 56:00.753
You're coming here?

56:00.754 --> 56:02.214
Sure, let's meet up.

56:02.923 --> 56:06.050
But, Mr. Cha, are you walking here?

56:06.051 --> 56:08.969
Wow, that's so close. I'll see you in 10--

56:08.970 --> 56:11.098
Ms. Kim wants you in her office.

56:12.182 --> 56:14.600
Me? Um…

56:14.601 --> 56:16.769
Oh. Sorry, but can you wait--

56:16.770 --> 56:19.730
She wants to see you immediately.

56:19.731 --> 56:21.440
And it will take a while.

56:21.441 --> 56:22.484
Why?

56:25.445 --> 56:31.325
I'm sorry, something came up.
I don't think we can meet today.

56:31.326 --> 56:32.953
I'll call you later. Bye.

56:33.787 --> 56:36.123
Why is she asking for me?

56:39.501 --> 56:41.169
You'll know when you get there.

56:42.462 --> 56:43.839
Did I do something wrong?

56:48.009 --> 56:49.970
Excuse me.

56:50.554 --> 56:51.847
I heard you were…

56:52.681 --> 56:55.392
looking for me…

56:56.351 --> 56:57.601
Where is she?

56:59.604 --> 57:03.984
Mmm… Then I'll refer to the dancheong
we saw today and…

57:04.568 --> 57:06.360
- Hey, Donggu.
- Hey!

57:06.361 --> 57:07.695
Were you practicing soccer?

57:07.696 --> 57:09.572
- Yes. But, Chan…
- Yes?

57:09.573 --> 57:12.032
This thing you did with the ball.

57:12.033 --> 57:14.618
Can you show us again?

57:14.619 --> 57:15.912
Again?

57:16.496 --> 57:17.956
Hmm.

57:19.374 --> 57:21.542
Since my dear Donggu is asking,

57:21.543 --> 57:23.169
- of course, I'll do it for you.
- Yes!

57:23.170 --> 57:25.463
Watch.

57:25.464 --> 57:26.714
Here.

57:27.924 --> 57:30.718
- You're so good. Wow!
- You're amazing.

57:30.719 --> 57:32.052
You're like Son Heungmin!

57:32.053 --> 57:33.846
Nice, Donggu.

57:35.182 --> 57:38.601
But my shoes aren't comfy,
and I'm with someone today,

57:38.602 --> 57:40.311
- so that's it for today.
-  Okay.

57:40.312 --> 57:41.645
Here you go.

57:41.646 --> 57:43.189
- See you later.
-  Okay.

57:43.190 --> 57:44.523
Bye.

57:44.524 --> 57:46.025
- Bye.
-  Bye.

57:46.026 --> 57:47.360
Bye.

57:48.069 --> 57:49.863
Let's go have pizza!

57:50.447 --> 57:52.698
He's Kim Donggu.
He lives in the neighborhood.

57:52.699 --> 57:55.451
We started talking and grew close.
We really clicked.

57:55.452 --> 57:57.871
Hang on.

57:59.206 --> 58:02.750
It's Je Raemee.
It's about our bowling game.

58:02.751 --> 58:05.670
You really are a human capybara.

58:06.671 --> 58:09.965
A capybara?
The animal that looks like a huge rat?

58:09.966 --> 58:14.637
Well… I've never heard
that I look like a rat before.

58:14.638 --> 58:18.682
Oh. I just meant how you get close
to everyone around you.

58:18.683 --> 58:20.769
Look it up. You're exactly the same.

58:25.690 --> 58:28.734
Anyway, thanks for everything today.
Let's head home now.

58:28.735 --> 58:29.986
I'll get going.

58:51.842 --> 58:54.761
Let me make it clear
since you seem to have misunderstood.

58:55.554 --> 58:58.890
It's true that I want
to get close to everyone.

58:59.975 --> 59:03.186
But I meant something else
when I asked us to be friends.

59:07.023 --> 59:08.275
I wanted to show you…

59:09.651 --> 59:11.152
that there's another way.

59:12.237 --> 59:15.406
At first, I was curious
why you were standing

59:15.407 --> 59:18.117
in front of that winter painting
by yourself.

59:18.118 --> 59:20.953
And while working with you
and watching you,

59:20.954 --> 59:23.540
I thought that perhaps…

59:24.541 --> 59:28.879
you thought the person standing alone
in that painting was you.

59:33.258 --> 59:37.304
So I know it's not my place,
but I wanted to show you something…

59:40.223 --> 59:42.058
that someone else showed me before.

59:43.435 --> 59:47.771
You know, I used to go to bed
every night as a child

59:47.772 --> 59:49.274
hoping that day would be the last.

59:50.734 --> 59:52.277
But I kept waking up,

59:53.069 --> 59:56.572
and I lived like a corpse…

59:56.573 --> 59:58.241
He's so weird.
Welcome him.

01:00:02.037 --> 01:00:03.413
No, he's a crazy guy.

01:00:05.832 --> 01:00:07.666
…with no hope, expression, or color.

01:00:11.254 --> 01:00:13.632
Then when I truly thought
it didn't matter if I died

01:00:14.549 --> 01:00:16.008
and decided to end everything…

01:00:22.307 --> 01:00:24.767
...someone suddenly talked to me.

01:00:24.768 --> 01:00:25.851
Purely by coincidence.

01:00:25.852 --> 01:00:27.187
"You're…

01:00:29.940 --> 01:00:31.523
my savior."

01:00:35.570 --> 01:00:37.113
Congratulations, and…

01:00:38.323 --> 01:00:39.824
you…

01:00:42.911 --> 01:00:46.164
saved me as well.

01:00:47.374 --> 01:00:50.210
That coincidence made me stop,

01:00:51.252 --> 01:00:53.755
and my daily life
started changing as well.

01:01:01.346 --> 01:01:04.598
I finally got the sketch sample
for my design.

01:01:04.599 --> 01:01:08.060
Make some noise!
It's all thanks to this pen.

01:01:08.061 --> 01:01:11.189
The words that person said to me
made me smile.

01:01:11.898 --> 01:01:14.943
Thank you for helping me
not give up on what I love.

01:01:15.610 --> 01:01:17.445
For giving me a reason to keep going.

01:01:18.196 --> 01:01:21.074
For the first time,
I started looking forward to the next day.

01:01:33.753 --> 01:01:34.796
And…

01:01:35.755 --> 01:01:37.757
I wanted to find a reason to keep going...

01:01:39.759 --> 01:01:44.139
...thanks to that person
who kept reaching out and talking to me.

01:02:00.613 --> 01:02:04.617
So… you can overcome it.

01:02:05.243 --> 01:02:06.786
Once you know how,

01:02:07.912 --> 01:02:10.123
you'll be able to escape on your own.

01:02:10.665 --> 01:02:14.877
I learned it through that person,
so I wanted to show you, too.

01:02:21.134 --> 01:02:22.844
I've also been trapped

01:02:23.428 --> 01:02:26.097
in a long winter all by myself.

01:02:31.102 --> 01:02:32.645
Is his name Mong?

01:02:34.272 --> 01:02:36.274
You're so cute, Mong.

01:02:37.484 --> 01:02:38.735
Let's take a picture.

01:02:39.819 --> 01:02:42.363
I can't hear on this side.

01:02:43.364 --> 01:02:44.948
I wanted to get close

01:02:44.949 --> 01:02:46.950
because you reminded me of my past.

01:02:48.328 --> 01:02:50.080
I'm sorry
if I made you uncomfortable.

01:02:50.497 --> 01:02:52.539
Three. Hey, Mong.
Look at the camera.

01:02:52.540 --> 01:02:55.042
- But I guess that doesn't matter.
- One, two, three.

01:03:00.256 --> 01:03:01.257
Excuse me!

01:03:03.093 --> 01:03:04.344
What?

01:03:05.804 --> 01:03:07.054
What is it?

01:03:07.055 --> 01:03:08.056
Take this.

01:03:09.682 --> 01:03:10.683
Oh…

01:03:12.811 --> 01:03:15.438
You didn't get to drink your favorite milk
because of me.

01:03:24.989 --> 01:03:28.493
Is your suggestion still valid?

01:03:29.077 --> 01:03:30.120
What?

01:03:30.703 --> 01:03:33.122
Hang on, I'll go over there.

01:03:34.415 --> 01:03:35.875
No, I'll go.

01:03:49.430 --> 01:03:51.891
Sorry, I didn't hear you.
What did you say?

01:03:52.517 --> 01:03:53.935
And what's with this milk?

01:03:54.936 --> 01:03:57.437
Is it still valid?

01:03:57.438 --> 01:03:58.439
What?

01:03:59.899 --> 01:04:01.567
Oh. The expiration date?

01:04:01.568 --> 01:04:02.777
Not the milk.

01:04:03.403 --> 01:04:06.280
I mean… being friends.

01:04:06.281 --> 01:04:07.949
The three-month trial.

01:04:09.075 --> 01:04:10.577
Is that still valid?

01:04:14.998 --> 01:04:16.708
I'd like to learn.

01:04:17.500 --> 01:04:19.252
Can you show me?

01:04:20.920 --> 01:04:24.215
You said someone showed you
how to escape from winter.

01:04:29.012 --> 01:04:30.095
Uh…

01:04:30.096 --> 01:04:31.973
I guess I'm too late.

01:04:33.057 --> 01:04:36.268
I understand.
I was so cruel to you.

01:04:36.269 --> 01:04:38.937
I'm so pathetic,
going back and forth like this.

01:04:38.938 --> 01:04:42.232
I'm just curious
whether I can change as well.

01:04:42.233 --> 01:04:46.446
And I thought it would be okay
if there's a time limit.

01:04:47.363 --> 01:04:49.448
Never mind. Just forget--

01:04:49.449 --> 01:04:50.658
It's valid.

01:04:54.120 --> 01:04:55.914
It's still valid.

01:04:56.831 --> 01:04:57.832
Ah…

01:04:58.833 --> 01:05:00.293
It's valid…

01:05:02.128 --> 01:05:04.130
Well, I…

01:05:05.256 --> 01:05:09.801
The nurse told me
that if I keep this on for too long,

01:05:09.802 --> 01:05:13.056
I wouldn't be able to heal naturally.

01:05:13.723 --> 01:05:15.098
So I thought

01:05:15.099 --> 01:05:17.769
I shouldn't stay trapped
behind my own barriers…

01:05:18.603 --> 01:05:21.897
I'm saying this because I…

01:05:21.898 --> 01:05:26.653
Then, it's okay
to be really nice to you now, right?

01:05:30.615 --> 01:05:31.616
Just three months.

01:05:32.575 --> 01:05:33.826
A trial period.

01:05:36.454 --> 01:05:38.747
I'll do my best to learn, too.

01:05:42.085 --> 01:05:43.086
Okay.

01:05:44.504 --> 01:05:46.171
Then let's do this.

01:05:46.172 --> 01:05:48.174
It'll be like we're on a spring picnic.

01:05:48.841 --> 01:05:49.884
Let's have fun.

01:06:28.464 --> 01:06:30.216
IN YOUR RADIANT SEASON

01:06:54.282 --> 01:06:56.408
It was my first time
hearing that sound.

01:06:56.409 --> 01:06:59.578
What if there is still
an empty spot in your memories

01:06:59.579 --> 01:07:01.038
that you're not aware of?

01:07:01.039 --> 01:07:04.291
I told you a secret,
so next time it's your turn.

01:07:04.292 --> 01:07:07.169
It seemed like
she might have dementia.

01:07:07.170 --> 01:07:10.464
So please…
Keep this a secret for now.

01:07:10.465 --> 01:07:12.758
It can't be, right?

01:07:12.759 --> 01:07:15.344
You have a crush
on Ms. Song, don't you?

01:07:15.345 --> 01:07:16.720
"That person"?

01:07:16.721 --> 01:07:18.555
I…

01:07:18.556 --> 01:07:20.266
...shouldn't have asked you for a ride.

01:07:21.100 --> 01:07:24.228
As long as she becomes happy,
I don't care what happens.

01:07:36.240 --> 01:07:37.324
IN YOUR RADIANT SEASON

01:07:37.325 --> 01:07:38.326
Translated by Juyoung Park
